{"nodes": [{"id": "specs_2026_06_08_prototype_pixel_port_design", "label": "Prototype Pixel-Port Design Spec", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-08-prototype-pixel-port-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_08_prototype_pixel_port_design_pixel_port_approach", "label": "Verbatim Pixel-Port Approach", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-08-prototype-pixel-port-design.md", "source_location": "Two locked decisions", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Drop @cloudscape-design/components entirely and copy the prototype's cloudscape.css + theme.css verbatim, rebuilding each page as plain JSX, because this is 'the only path to genuine pixel parity'. Second locked decision: keep all real backend integration (api.ts/types.ts data flow), with prototype mock data-*.js as reference only except the intentional localStorage contracts tf9-color-mode and tf9-repo-overrides. Supersedes the earlier Cloudscape-approximation approach."}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_08_prototype_pixel_port_design_fouc_theme_init", "label": "FOUC-preventing Theme Init (tf9-color-mode)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-08-prototype-pixel-port-design.md", "source_location": "Foundation", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Inline <head> script reads localStorage tf9-color-mode before first paint and sets html[data-theme] to avoid a flash of the wrong theme; default follows prefers-color-scheme. The same contract is embedded in the prototype report pages and in generated standalone HTML reports so they theme-match the SPA."}], "edges": [{"source": "specs_2026_06_08_prototype_pixel_port_design", "target": "runs_runs", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0